        "created_at": "2025-05-26T05:59:41.621Z",
        "cooked": "<p>While I do appreciate the new ‚ÄúScreen security‚Äù  setting and what you are trying to do, this has unfortunatly caused issues at the company where I work.</p>\n<p>We are using Omnissa Horizon (Formaly VMware Horizon) VDI infrastructure where our employees only have a thin client at their desk and are connecting to a virtual desktop running Windows 11.<br>\nMany of our employees are using Signal on their desktop, but the Screen security feature makes Signal just become a black box.<br>\nThe users cannot turn it off, since they can‚Äôt  access the settings.<br>\nI don‚Äôt know why Horizon triggers this feature, but it does.</p>\n<p>It would be great if there was a command line option so that we could turn it off. Alternatively be able to access the settings or have some other way to turn it off.</p>\n<p>(We have already turned off the Microsoft Recall feature via Group Policy)</p>",
